July 6, 2005
Ms. Magalie Roman Salas, Secretary Federal Energy Regulatory Commission Office of the Secretary, Room 1A 888 First Street, N.E. Washington, D.C. 20426
Re: The Legacy Energy Group, LLC updated Market Power Analysis Report and Revised Market Based FERC Electric Rate Schedule No. 1 as required by Commission order issued May 21, 2005 ER98-3809-000
Dear Ms. Salas:
Please find enclosed for filing one electronic (disk) and one original and six copies of the “Updated Market Power Analysis Report” and “Revised Market Based Tariff Rate” as approved in Docket # ER99-1719-000 for acceptance per Commission Regulations. As required by Commission Regulations we are submitting a Notice of Filing and a copy of the Notice of Filing on the enclosed disk along with a copy of the Updated Market Power Analysis Report and Revised Market Based FERC Electric Rate Schedule No. 1.
Please let me know if there are other requirements or anything else we need to do to complete our obligations under ER98-3809-000.
Sincerely,
Michael L.R. Housley President
Enclosures
POWER SALES BY THE LEGACY ENERGY GROUP, LLC (LEGACY)
Revised FERC ELECTRIC RATE SCHEDULE NO. 1
1. Availability
The Legacy Energy Group, LLC (Legacy) makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale.
2. Applicability
This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by Legacy not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Legacy.
3. Rates
All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Legacy.
4. Other Terms and Conditions
All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Legacy.
5. Affiliate Sales Prohibited
No sale may be made pursuant to this Rate Schedule to any public utility with a franchised electric service territory that is controlled by, or under common control with, or controlling Legacy.
6. Communications.
Except as otherwise agreed in writing by the parties to a transaction hereunder, any notice, demand or request provided for in this Tariff shall be deemed to be properly given or made if set forth in writing and delivered or sent by first-class mall, postage prepaid, to Seller at its principal office or to any purchaser when sales are made to wholesale purchasers under this Rate Schedule.
7. Duration
This Tariff shall continue in effect until terminated or changed and such termination or change becomes effective/n accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements.
8. Modification
Seller may unilaterally apply, under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and the regulations promulgated thereunder, to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this Tariff.
9. Changes in Status
Legacy must timely report to the Commission any change in status that would reflect a departure from the characteristics the Commission relied upon in granting market-based rate authority. A change in status includes, but is not limited to, each of the following: (i) ownership or control of generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production other than fuel supplies, or (ii) affiliation with any entity not disclosed in the application for market-based rate authority that owns or controls generation or transmission facilities or inputs to electric power production, or affiliation with any entity that has a franchised service area. Any change in status must be filed no later than 30 days after the change in status occurs.
10. Effective Date
The original Rate Schedule was effective on March 19, 1999. This revised Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Commission.
